Emergency services have reported that 16 people had been left injured on Monday afternoon following a collision between a light motor vehicle and a taxi on the N2 in eManzimtoti, KwaZulu-Natal.
ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement that paramedics from the service, along with VEMA and other services, arrived on the scene to find the taxi and light motor vehicle in the middle of the road. ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
